definitions.definition: Any of several marine molluscs of the order Octopoda , having no internal or external protective shell or bone (unlike the nautilus , squid and cuttlefish ) and eight arms each covered with suckers .
The flesh of these marine molluscs eaten as food.
An organization that has many powerful branches controlled from the centre.

main_definition: ( countable , loosely ) Any of several marine molluscs of the order Octopoda , having no internal or external protective shell or bone (unlike the nautilus , squid and cuttlefish ) and eight arms each covered with suckers .
secondary_definitions: ( countable , strictly ) A mollusc from genus Octopus .
( uncountable ) The flesh of these marine molluscs eaten as food.
( countable ) An organization that has many powerful branches controlled from the centre.
